“Pakistan has had to hire personnel with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear facilities; given the drop in educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people working in nuclear or missile programs,” Russian Foreign Ministry expert Yuri Korolev told a meeting with his American counterparts.
