The athlete, who works as a security agent and as an employee of the UPS company, has recently given bad news to his rivals, winning two gold medals at the amateur World Championships of the World Karate and Kickboxing Association (WKA), held from 23 to 30 October in Edinburgh, Scotland.
“I’ve won in the full-contact kickboxing and Thai-box categories,” he explained.
"I am currently preparing to participate in the San Shou World Cup in China."
“They will invite athletes who have finished in the top four in the last world championship in each category.”
"In 2009, I won the bronze medal in Toronto".
"In 2005, in Vietnam, I finished in eighth place."
