After Midnight, Young Koreans Cannot Play Online
The South Korean government will adopt a so-called "Cinderella" law that will prevent teenagers from participating in online games after midnight by blocking their access, government officials have said.
In December, a bill will be submitted to Parliament to ask online gaming companies to block access to such games after midnight for young people under the age of 16, according to representatives of the Ministries of Culture and Family.
